    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000, 9100, 9200, 9400, AND 9900 MODELS - SLEEPER LIGHTING AND
        ACCESSORIES - TROUBLESHOOTING - Bunk Speakers With 48 And 60 Inch Box Sleeper
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Bunk Speakers With 48 And 60 Inch Box Sleeper</title>
        <table id="t0820405" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Bunk Speakers With 48 and 60 Inch Box Sleeper</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.67in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.89in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.47in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (629) and measure resistance of front speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Across front speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>3.5 to 4.5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (117), and reconnect conn. (629). At (117) measure resistance across
                                circuits 86AD and 86AH.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(117), 86AD to 86AH.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>3.5 to 4.5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate short or open circuit condition, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect connector (630) and measure resistance of rear speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Across rear speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>3.5 to 4.5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective speaker.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Disconnect conn. (118), and reconnect conn. (630). At (118) measure resistance across
                                circuits 86AK and 86AL.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(118), 86AK to 86AL.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.5 to 4.5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate short or open circuit condition, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At conn. (117), on the volume control connector half side, measure resistance across
                                yellow and black wires.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(117), YL to BK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>45 to 55 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Repair or replace defective volume control.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At conn. (117) on the volume control conn. half side, measure resistance across yellow
                                and green wires with the volume control turned to its highest volume setting.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(117), YL to GN.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Repair or replace defective volume control, headset jack, or volume control
                                circuits.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At conn. (118), on the volume control conn. half side, measure resistance across red
                                and black wires.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(118), RD to BK.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>45 to 55 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Repair or replace defective volume control.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At conn. (118) on the volume control connector half side, measure resistance across
                                red and green wires with the volume control turned to its highest volume setting.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(118), RD to GN.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Repair or replace defective volume control, headset jack, or volume control
                                circuits.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At connector (117) measure resistance for circuit 86AB to 86AC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(117), 86AB to 86AC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate short condition, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At conn. (472) install a jumper wire between circuits 86AB and 86AC. At connector
                                (117) measure resistance for circuit 86AB to 86AC.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(117), 86AB to 86AC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60;2 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor conn. in circuit 86AB or 86AC, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At connector (118) measure resistance for circuit 86AP to 86AE.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(118,) 86AP to 86AE.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate short condition, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>At conn. (472) install a jumper wire between circuits 86AP and 86AE. At conn. (118)
                                measure resistance for circuit 86AP to 86AE.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>(118), 86AP to 86AE.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>&#60;2 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 86AP or 86AE, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>The headset circuits can be checked with an ohmmeter. Do the resistors measure
                                approximately 120 ohms?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Headset jack resistors.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Approx. 120 ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace defective resistor or replace volume control module.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Do the headset capacitors charge up and discharge when VOM meter is used to measure
                                their resistance?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Headset jack capacitors.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Replace shorted or open headset capacitor, or replace volume control module.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Bunk speaker circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
